[{"id":"VH902703","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two pure elements react to form a compound. One element is an alkali metal, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>X</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, and the other element is a halogen, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Z\"><math alttext=\"Z\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Z</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. Which of the following is the most valid scientific claim that can be made about the compound?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH902703_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">It has the formula <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X Z 2\"><math alttext=\"X Z 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>XZ</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">It does not dissolve in water.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">It contains ionic bonds.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">It contains covalent bonds.</p>"],"answer":2}]